docs.abstract: The Amazon chief’s split from his wife raises questions about the disposal of their enormous stake in the company he founded. Investors deserve answers.
docs.snippet: The Amazon chief’s split from his wife raises questions about the disposal of their enormous stake in the company he founded. Investors deserve answers.
docs.lead_paragraph: Jeff Bezos and his wife, MacKenzie, may be the first billionaire couple with a huge stake in an enormous technology company to announce their divorce.

headline.main: Why Jeff Bezos’ Divorce Should Worry Amazon Investors
headline.print_headline: As Bezoses Split, Risks For Investors

docs.abstract: The once mighty cable giant is paying $340 million for the free, advertising-based service, which has about 12 million active viewers a month.
docs.snippet: The once mighty cable giant is paying $340 million for the free, advertising-based service, which has about 12 million active viewers a month.
docs.lead_paragraph: Viacom, the once mighty cable giant behind pop culture confections like “Jersey Shore” and children’s fare like “Dora the Explorer,” is acquiring the streaming service PlutoTV for $340 million, the companies said in an announcement on Tuesday.

headline.main: Viacom Buys PlutoTV Streaming Service, Its Biggest Digital Push Yet
headline.print_headline: Viacom Acquires PlutoTV Streaming Service, Its Biggest Digital Push Yet

docs.abstract: A year after the Trump administration tried to help American manufacturers of laundry equipment, prices are up, sales have fallen and stock prices are down.
docs.snippet: A year after the Trump administration tried to help American manufacturers of laundry equipment, prices are up, sales have fallen and stock prices are down.
docs.lead_paragraph: You may not have appreciated it at the time — golden eras have a habit of coming and going like that — but a five-year stretch that started in 2013 was a pretty great time to buy a washing machine.

headline.main: How Tariffs Stained the Washing Machine Market
headline.print_headline: Tariffs Tossed a Market  Right Into a Spin Cycle

docs.abstract: In public, executives wring their hands over automation’s negative consequences for workers. In private, they talk about how they are racing to automate.
docs.snippet: In public, executives wring their hands over automation’s negative consequences for workers. In private, they talk about how they are racing to automate.
docs.lead_paragraph: DAVOS, Switzerland — They’ll never admit it in public, but many of your bosses want machines to replace you as soon as possible.

headline.main: The Hidden Automation Agenda of the Davos Elite
headline.print_headline: The Automation Agenda Hidden by the Davos Elite

docs.abstract: Since Brian Krzanich, who was chief executive for five years, was forced out in June, the chip maker has been looking for a new boss.
docs.snippet: Since Brian Krzanich, who was chief executive for five years, was forced out in June, the chip maker has been looking for a new boss.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Intel answered many questions from Wall Street Thursday, but not the one that has dogged the company for seven months: Who will become chief executive of the giant chip maker?

headline.main: Intel Searches (and Searches) for a New C.E.O.
headline.print_headline: Intel Is Still Seeking a Seasoned Executive to Lead Company

docs.abstract: Deutsche Bank and Commerzbank said the risks outweighed the benefits of trying to create a mega-bank capable of taking on Wall Street giants.
docs.snippet: Deutsche Bank and Commerzbank said the risks outweighed the benefits of trying to create a mega-bank capable of taking on Wall Street giants.
docs.lead_paragraph: FRANKFURT — Deutsche Bank and Commerzbank abruptly called off their merger talks Thursday, saying they concluded that the perils of trying to forge a megabank with international clout outweighed the potential benefits.

headline.main: Germany’s Troubled Banking Giants Decide Against a Merger
headline.print_headline: Germany’s Top Banks Decide Against Merger

docs.abstract: Student demand for computer science courses is outstripping the supply of professors, creating a student divide of computing haves and have-nots.
docs.snippet: Student demand for computer science courses is outstripping the supply of professors, creating a student divide of computing haves and have-nots.
docs.lead_paragraph: Lured by the prospect of high-salary, high-status jobs, college students are rushing in record numbers to study computer science.

headline.main: The Hard Part of Computer Science? Getting Into Class
headline.print_headline: Hard Part of Computer Science Class? Getting In

docs.abstract: Facebook’s second in command wanted an examination of the billionaire’s financial ties after he delivered a blistering speech about tech companies.
docs.snippet: Facebook’s second in command wanted an examination of the billionaire’s financial ties after he delivered a blistering speech about tech companies.
docs.lead_paragraph: Sheryl Sandberg asked Facebook’s communications staff to research George Soros’s financial interests in the wake of his high-profile attacks on tech companies, according to three people with knowledge of her request, indicating that Facebook’s second in command was directly involved in the social network’s response to the liberal billionaire.

headline.main: Sheryl Sandberg Asked for Soros Research, Facebook Acknowledges
headline.print_headline: Sandberg Asked Staff To Research Soros Links

docs.abstract: Mr. Zuckerberg said that he wouldn’t step down as chairman and that his No. 2, Sheryl Sandberg, was “doing great work” despite questions about their management.
docs.snippet: Mr. Zuckerberg said that he wouldn’t step down as chairman and that his No. 2, Sheryl Sandberg, was “doing great work” despite questions about their management.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — On Thursday, Mark Zuckerberg, Facebook’s chief executive and chairman, held a conference call with reporters to discuss how the social network manages problematic posts and its community standards.

headline.main: Mark Zuckerberg Defends Facebook as Furor Over Its Tactics Grows
headline.print_headline: Zuckerberg on Defense Amid Furor Over Tactics

docs.abstract: The automakers need each other, but they also need a bold leader to secure their future.
docs.snippet: The automakers need each other, but they also need a bold leader to secure their future.
docs.lead_paragraph: Renault, Nissan and Mitsubishi, on their own, aren’t among the top handful of the world’s auto manufacturers. Together, in a unique alliance, however, they outmatch the sales of giant automakers like Volkswagen.

headline.main: What’s Next for the Renault-Nissan Alliance?
headline.print_headline: Automakers Need Each Other  And Strong Leader for Future
